Over this weekend I have had the chance to do two things that I care about deeply. First is being able to help young boys and girls get excited about STEM, esspecially those that wouldn't otheriwse think they could, the second is being on the airwave via radio!
On saturday I volunteered with Boys at Tulane in STEM! (BATS!) which provided the oppouruinty for boys in middle school to meet and work with undergraduate, graduate, faculty, and professional role models in STEM fields. The day was filled with workshops that were creative and fun, I learned and had as much fun as the young boys. My task as group leader was to take the boys between their workshops and aid in any way that I can. Right from the beginning I could tell that this was 
